Mesoscutum (
Fig. 42
) variably distinctly carinate mediolongitudinally at least partly over anteromedial lobe and often through depressed posteromedial region, sometimes to or near posterior margin of mesoscutum; scutellar-axillar complex with axillae meshlike reticulate but scutellum with more longitudinally aligned sculpture so as to appear more reticulate-strigose. Front leg dark except tarsus usually lighter, more orangish. Middle leg (
Fig. 34
) dark except trochantellus dorsally and ventroapically white, and femur apically or knee narrowly pale to white; femur uniformly setose over about apical half (
Fig. 50
); tibia with 6–8 pegs in two or more rows forming distinct patch (
Fig. 48
