Fig. 43
), but sometimes white setae extending more extensively posteriorly to or near mediocubital fold over infuscate region (
Fig. 44
) or disc with variably large region of hairlike white setae adjacent to mediocubital fold behind posterobasal angle of anterior hyaline region, with the white setae sometimes extending anteriorly into infuscate region separating anterior hyaline region from mediocubital fold, and then wing with oblique, more or less hourglass-shaped region of white setae medially constricted by dark, slender-lanceolate setae (
Fig. 45
