Fig. 46
). Propodeum (
Fig. 41
) elongate medially, with ∩-like incurved foramen distant from shallowly, broadly Vlike angulate anterior margin, and mostly reticulate-rugose to obliquely strigose but minutely granular posteriorly.

Gaster (
Fig. 47
) mostly brown dorsally, but under some angles of light with blue to purple or reddishviolaceous lusters basally on Gt1 and usually increasingly more apparent and extensive laterally on Gt1–Gt5, with Gt6 mostly or entirely with distinct blue to purple luster; Gt6 reticulate to reticulate-rugose or reticulate-imbricate. Ovipositor sheaths shorter than metatibia (
Fig. 34
